    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1955-07-19T15:53:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1955-07-19T15:53:00-05:00" n="163"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d163">
                <head>163. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Secretary of State, at Geneva</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d163fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 684a.86/7–1955. Top Secret; Limited Distribution. Drafted, approved,
                        and signed by <persName corresp="#p_HHJ1">Hoover</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,<date calendar="gregorian" when="1955-07-19T15:53:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 19, 1955—3:53 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Tedul1">Tedul</gloss> 23. Alpha and Middle East. Eyes only
                    Secretary from Acting Secretary. Re <gloss target="#t_Dulte1">Dulte</gloss>
                        15,<note n="2" xml:id="d163fn2">See the editorial note,<ref target="#d162">
                            <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>
                        </ref>.</note>
                    <gloss target="#t_Secto1">Secto</gloss> 28.<note n="3" xml:id="d163fn3">
                        <ref target="#d161">Document 161</ref>.</note>
                    <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>No tanks of any type have been scheduled by US for Iraqis, and
                            suggestion of <persName corresp="#p_ESA1">Eden</persName> that <gloss
                                target="#t_UK1">UK</gloss> should supply Centurions (at US expense)
                            was first intimated to us by <persName corresp="#p_MSRM1"
                                >Makins</persName> in US–<gloss target="#t_UK1">UK</gloss>
                            <gloss target="#t_ME1">ME</gloss> strategy talks two weeks ago. We made
                            no comment.</item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>Iraqis have not indicated they want us to obtain Brit tanks for them.
                            We understand they prefer US equipment.</item>
                        <label>3.</label>
                        <item>In view broad effect which your talks at Geneva may have upon future
                            joint US–<gloss target="#t_UK1">UK</gloss> plans for <gloss
                                target="#t_ME1">ME</gloss> defense, we are suggesting to <persName
                                corresp="#p_MSRM1">Makins</persName> that continuation of <gloss
                                target="#t_ME1">ME</gloss> strategy talks which are scheduled for
                            this week should be postponed until after Geneva conference has been
                                concluded.<gloss target="#t_UK1">UK</gloss> had presented its
                            concepts two weeks ago, which could involve us in substantially
                            stepped-up expenditures. We had expected to present our position this
                            week but under circumstances will defer for further
                            consideration.</item>
                        <label>4.</label>
                        <item>No further developments on Alpha here.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HHJ1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Hoover</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
